parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission line failure can cause oil leaks, smoke, and potentially lead to a fire, which can result in accidents or injuries.
Transmission slipping and failure can cause loss of power, sudden acceleration, and difficulty shifting gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Transmission control module failure can cause erratic transmission behavior, leading to accidents or difficulty controlling the vehicle.
symptoms: controls between steering wheel and dash shorting out

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission safety interlock failure can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle moves without pressing the pedal

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat belts to retract can cause the belt to become twisted, stuck, or loose, reducing the effectiveness of the restraint system and increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The front seat belts will not retract
or bind up in the guide system
causing the belt to become stuck or loose
making it difficult or impossible to use the seatbelt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The twisting or misalignment of the seat belts can cause the belt to become loose or unsecure, reducing the effectiveness of the restraint system and increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belts twist when trying to fasten
causing the belt to become loose or unsecure
or the belt threads are installed backwards
requiring the belt to be twisted to buckle correctly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the integrated child safety seat can cause the child to fall forward with ease, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The integrated child safety seat sits too erect
allowing the child to fall forward with ease
or the plastic retainer clip will not stay fastened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving, leading to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stop and resume at will
windshield wipers are inactive for extended periods
windshield wipers fail to oscillate properly
windshield wipers only work when the windshield is very wet.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear window or hatch glass can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially injure occupants.
symptoms: Rear window falls out of the vehicle
rear window blows out while driving
rear hatch latch glass cracks or shatters.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or failed engagement of gears can cause accidents, loss of control, or stranding.
symptoms: failure to engage into forward and reverse

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling or shut-off can cause loss of power steering and braking, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling or shut-off while driving
loss of power steering and braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked exhaust manifolds can cause stalling, carbon monoxide poisoning, and engine failure.
Engine fires can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
PGR valve failure can cause engine shut-off, loss of power braking and steering, and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: loss of power braking and steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause battery drain, starter failure, and alternator failure.
The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, leading to safety risks, such as engine stalling, loss of power, and even fires.
symptoms: Windshield wipers (front and back) work sporadically
vehicle jolts when going up large hills
computer chip shutting down the vehicle
and smoke coming from under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose or damaged wiring and harnesses can cause electrical system failures, leading to safety risks, such as engine stalling, loss of power, and even fires.
symptoms: Windshield wipers (front and back) work sporadically
vehicle jolts when going up large hills
smoke coming from under the hood

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and failure can cause loss of power and control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: and smoke coming from under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause loss of power and control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: and vehicle jolts when going up large hills.
